Are you passionate about analyzing data to drive business success, and eager to dive deep into the world of AI-driven software development? Join Renn Labs, where your enthusiasm meets high-energy, collaborative, and forward-thinking tech innovation. We're on the lookout for skilled Data Analysts to play a pivotal role in our data-driven approaches and providing timely insights. This is more than a job – it's a chance to be at the forefront of technological advancement with a team that values creativity and innovation.

The Data Analyst is a crucial role, responsible for collaborating effectively with key stakeholders, product management teams, digital marketers, data scientists, and data engineers to establish and implement best practices in data analytics and data visualization. This position plays a central part in ensuring both innovation and excellence in our technology solutions that leverage both our and our client's business performance.

Ready to elevate your value to new heights and redefine the future? Uplift your Data Analytics journey with Renn Labs today.

IN DETAIL, YOUR SUCCESS IN THIS JOB WILL BE


 * Efficiently analyze datasets to identify trends, patterns, and insights;
 * Seamlessly develop, maintain, and automate dashboards to track key metrics;
 * Proactively collaborate with marketing team and data scientists to implement innovative data solutions that support data-driven campaigns;
 * Continuously ensure impeccable data quality, integrity, and security across all data systems;
 * Timely monitor and troubleshoot data systems to ensure optimal performance and exceptional reliability;
 * Diligently develop and maintain comprehensive documentation for data processes, systems, and standards;
 * Rigorously implement stringent data governance and compliance measures to meet regulatory requirements;
 * Constantly evaluate and improve cutting-edge data analysis tools and technologies to keep our and our client's platform competitive and innovative.



What You’ll Need For Success In This Job


 * Bachelor's degree or higher degree in Data Science, Statistics, Maths, Economics, Computer Science, a related field, or equivalent practical experience;
 * Proven experience as a Data Analyst or in a similar role for at least 3 years, with a focus on eCommerce and Data Operations;
 * Strong proficiency in data analysis tools such as SQL, Python, or R, and analytics tools (e.g., Google Analytics);
 * Experience with eCommerce platforms (e.g., Shopify) and marketing platforms (e.g., Hubspot).
 * Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or Looker;
 * Familiarity of digital marketing metrics, including SEO, SEM, and social media analytics;
 * Strong passion for staying up-to-date with the latest trends and best practices;
 * Good communication, with the ability to understand business requirements and comfortably discuss ideas;
 * Excellent collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively in a global environment and agile project setting;
 * Solid analytical thinking, problem-solving skills, high attention to detail and accuracy in work delivery;
 * Demonstrated ability in mentoring and managing multiple projects simultaneously will set your application apart and give you a distinct advantage;
 * Last but not least, an eagerness to learn and a startup spirit at heart. This role provides extensive exposure to AI-driven product development, offering a pathway to advance in the future of technology.



